#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1000
#, 
msgid "Notes on Building Software"
msgstr "Remarques sur la construction de logiciels"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1001
#, 
msgid "Those people who have built an LFS system may be aware of the general principles of downloading and unpacking software."
msgstr "Il se peut que les gens qui ont construit un système LFS connaissent les principes généraux du téléchargement et du déballage de logiciel."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1002
#, 
msgid "Some of that information is repeated here for those new to building their own software."
msgstr "Certaines de ces informations sont répétées ici pour les nouveaux qui construisent leurs propres logiciels."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1003
#, 
msgid "Each set of installation instructions contains a URL from which you can download the package."
msgstr "Chaque groupe d'instructions d'installation contient une adresse Web depuis laquelle vous pouvez télécharger le paquet."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1004
#, 
msgid "The patches; however, are stored on the LFS servers and are available via HTTP."
msgstr "Les correctifs; cependant, sont enregistrés sur les serveurs LFS et sont disponibles via HTTP."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1005
#, 
msgid "These are referenced as needed in the installation instructions."
msgstr "Ils sont référencés comme nécessaires dans les instructions d'installation."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1006
#, fuzzy
msgid "While you can keep the source files anywhere you like, we assume that you have unpacked the package and changed into the directory created by the unpacking process (the 'build' directory)."
msgstr "Si vous pouvez mettre les fichiers sources là où vous voulez, nous supposons que vous avez déballé le paquet et êtes allé dans le répertoire créé par le processus de déballage (the 'build' directory)."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1007
#, 
msgid "We also assume you have uncompressed any required patches and they are in the directory immediately above the 'build' directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1008
#, 
msgid "We can not emphasize strongly enough that you should start from a"
msgstr "Nous ne saurions que trop vous recommander fortement de démarrer à partir d'une"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1009
#, 
msgid "clean source tree"
msgstr "arborescence de sources propre"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1010
#, 
msgid "each time."
msgstr "à chaque fois."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1011
#, 
msgid "This means that if you have had an error during configuration or compilation, it's usually best to delete the source tree and re-unpack it"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1012
#, 
msgid "before"
msgstr "avant"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1013
#, 
msgid "trying again."
msgstr "de réessayer."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:100-1014
#, 
msgid "This obviously doesn't apply if you're an advanced user used to hacking _F27_ s and C code, but if in doubt, start from a clean tree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:110-1000
#, fuzzy
msgid "Building Software as an Unprivileged (non-root) User"
msgstr "Construction de logiciels en tant qu'utilisateur non privilégié (non root) User"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:110-1001
#, 
msgid "The golden rule of Unix System Administration is to use your superpowers only when necessary."
msgstr "La règle d'or de l'administration d'un système Unix est de n'utiliser vos super-pouvoirs que si nécessaire."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:110-1002
#, 
msgid "Hence, BLFS recommends that you build software as an unprivileged user and only become the _U3_ user when installing the software."
msgstr "D'où la recommandation de BLFS de construire les logiciels en tant qu'utilisateur non privilégié et de ne devenir l'utilisateur _U3_ que lors de l'installation du logiciel."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:110-1003
#, 
msgid "This philosophy is followed in all the packages in this book."
msgstr "On suit cette philosophie dans tous les paquets du livre."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:110-1004
#, 
msgid "Unless otherwise specified, all instructions should be executed as an unprivileged user."
msgstr "Sauf spécifications contraires, toutes les instructions devraient être exécutées en tant qu'utilisateur non privilégié."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:110-1005
#, 
msgid "The book will advise you on instructions that need _U3_ privileges."
msgstr "Le livre vous conseillera sur les instructions qui ont besoin des privilèges _U3_."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:120-1000
#, 
msgid "Unpacking the Software"
msgstr "Déballer le logiciel"

