#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:170-1001
#, 
msgid "For each package described, BLFS lists the known dependencies."
msgstr "Pour chaque paquet décrit, BLFS liste les dépendances connues."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:170-1002
#, 
msgid "These are listed under several headings, whose meaning is as follows:"
msgstr "Elles sont listées sous plusieurs en-têtes, dont la signification est la suivante :"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:170-1003
#, 
msgid "Required"
msgstr "Requises"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:170-1004
#, 
msgid "means that the target package cannot be correctly built without the dependency having first been installed."
msgstr "signifie que le paquet cible ne peut pas se construire correctement sans avoir d'abord installé la dépendance."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:170-1005
#, 
msgid "Recommended"
msgstr "Recommandées"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:170-1006
#, 
msgid "means that BLFS strongly suggests this package is installed first for a clean and trouble-free build, that won't have issues either during the build process, or at run-time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:170-1007
#, 
msgid "The instructions in the book assume these packages are installed."
msgstr "Les instructions dans le livre considèrent que ses paquets sont installés."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:170-1008
#, 
msgid "Some changes or workarounds may be required if these packages are not installed."
msgstr "Des modifications ou contournements peuvent être requis si ces paquets ne sont pas installés."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:170-1009
#, 
msgid "Optional"
msgstr "Optionnelles"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:170-1010
#, 
msgid "means that this package might be installed for added functionality."
msgstr "signifie que ce paquet pourrait être installé pour ajouter des fonctions."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:170-1011
#, 
msgid "Often BLFS will describe the dependency to explain the added functionality that will result."
msgstr "BLFS décrira souvent la dépendance pour expliquer la fonctionnalité supplémentaire résultante."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:180-1000
#, 
msgid "Using the Most Current Package Sources"
msgstr "Utilisation de paquets sources plus récents"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:180-1001
#, 
msgid "On occasion you may run into a situation in the book when a package will not build or work properly."
msgstr "Occasionnellement, dans le livre, vous pourrez être dans la situation ou un paquet ne se construit pas ou ne fonctionne pas correctement."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:180-1002
#, 
msgid "Though the Editors attempt to ensure that every package in the book builds and works properly, sometimes a package has been overlooked or was not tested with this particular version of BLFS."
msgstr "Bien que les éditeurs tentent de faire en sorte que chaque paquet dans le livre se construise et fonctionne correctement, parfois un paquet a été oublié ou n'a pas été testé avec cette version particulière de BLFS."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/building-notes.xml.1.chaine:180-1003
#, 
msgid "If you discover that a package will not build or work properly, you should see if there is a more current version of the package."
msgstr "Si vous découvrez un paquet qui ne se construit pas ou ne fonctionne pas correctement, vous pouvez regarder s'il s'agit de la version la plus récente du paquet."

#. type: Content of: 
